-- A tropical rain forest project is to start soon in south China's Hainan province.
-- China's largest tropical rain forest, in the Xishuangbanna nature reserve in Yunnan Province, will get further protection when the reserve is enlarged from 247,000 ha to 533,000 ha.
Under the program tropical rain-forest trees will be planted, along with tropical fruit trees and economic trees.
The ATO, set up in 1976, comprises Angola, Tanzania, Liberia, The Central African Republic, Cameroon, Nigeria, Zaire, the Congo, Corte D'Ivoire, Gabon, Sao Tome and Principe, Ghana, Equatorial Guinea.
